Beers - Producer  \n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r1033100}}\n\n[[Category:1990 debut albums]]\n[[Category:Absent Friends (band) albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{use dmy dates|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Here's Looking Up Your Address\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Absent Friends (band)|Absent Friends]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 6 April 1990\n| recorded   = 1989\n| studio     = Paradise Studios, Rhinoceros Studios, Sydney, Australia\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Rock music|Rock]]\n| length     =\n| label      = [[RooART]]\n| producer   = [[Garry Gary Beers|Garry Beers]], [[Sean Kelly (Australian musician)|Sean Kelly]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = Networking\n| next_year  = 1990\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Here's Looking Up Your Address\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Hallelujah\n | single1date = November 1989\n | single2     = Hullabaloo\n | single2date = February 1990\n | single3     = [[I Don't Want To Be With Nobody But You]]\n | single3date = April 1990\n | single4     = Harmony\n | single4date = August 1990\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Here's Looking Up Your Address''''' is the debut studio album by [[Australia]]n [[Rock music|rock]] band [[Absent Friends (band)|Absent Friends]] and was released in April 1990 on the [[RooART]] label, with national distribution through BMG Music. The album entered the Australian Album Charts on 9 April 1990, peaking at No.7 and stayed in the charts for 24 weeks. ''Here's Looking Up Your Address'' went on to be certified gold. It was re-released by RooART in October 2005.  \n\n==Track listing==\nAll songs written by S. Kelly except where noted, according to [[Australasian Performing Right Association]] (APRA).<ref name=\"APRA\">{{cite web|url=http://www.apra.com.au/cms/worksearch/worksearch.srvlt |title=Australasian Performing Right Association |publisher=[[Australasian Performing Right Associati